      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:4:43:5",
      "text": [
        " ازْدَحَمَ النَّاسُ يَوْمَ الْجُمُعَةِ فِي إِمْرَةِ عَلِيٍّ ( عليه السلام ) بِالْكُوفَةِ فَقَتَلُوا رَجُلًا فَوَدَى دِيَتَهُ إِلَى أَهْلِهِ مِنْ بَيْتِ مَالِ الْمُسْلِمِينَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Ibn Mahboub, from Abu Ayoub, from Muhammad Bin Muslim, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Ja’far<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘(Whenever) the people thronged on the day of Friday during the emirate of Ali<sup>asws</sup> at Al-Kufa, so a man got killed, his wergild was paid to his family from the public treasury of the Muslims’."
        ]
      }
    },
